le":"Naiskohtaloita","original_language":"fi"},{"id":858918,"adult":false,"title":"One Summer","video":false,"overview":"Jack takes his son and daughter to his late wife's beachside hometown hoping to heal and become closer. The summer brings visions of the past that could forge a new path forward.","genre_ids":[10770,18,10751,10749],"popularity":0.588,"vote_count":24,"poster_path":"/yRjSB2Uq3EwGn2ej0I8H78hWaCy.jpg","release_date":"2021-10-03","vote_average":7.4,"backdrop_path":"/cnlHvcjeAuzZFTAMfYSNnf7g6eA.jpg","original_title":"One Summer","original_language":"en"},{"id":5527,"adult":false,"title":"A Killing Affair","video":false,"overview":"Peter Weller stars as Baton Morris, a drifter suspected of murder, in this crime drama. A widow (Kathy Baker) living in West Virginia takes in the man (Weller) whom she believes murdered her husband. As she spends more time with him, she begins to fall for him, but continues to question whether or not she can trust him. Directed by David Saperstein and based on a novel by Robert Houston, A Killing Affair features twists and turns up until the end.","genre_ids":[18,53,80],"popularity":0.2891,"vote_count":1,"poster_path":"/ws5Hz7Sh6GrN06fMeJeorqjRxP2.jpg","release_date":"1985-10-24","vote_average":6,"backdrop_path":"/j8n8so85LgbjlMCxl9CzhC4vIkE.jpg","original_title":"A Killing Affair","original_language":"en"},{"id":1062323,"adult":false,"title":"The Champion","video":false,"overview":"Diego has just been voted best young player in Europe and at the age of 20 he is on his way to making his team, Atlético de Madrid, champions of La Liga. But his impulsive and conflictive character makes the club, fed up with his excesses, hire Álex, a withdrawn and lonely psychology professor, to improve his behaviour. The two will have no choice but to learn to understand each other.","genre_ids":[18,10751,35],"popularity":0.5631,"vote_count":45,"poster_path":"/wBftPyDCfxZ9XD5J5X6LYzFzZYK.jpg","release_date":"2024-07-12","vote_average":5.356,"backdrop_path":"/sRuoaYjWLLngZo2XYKPwyL9SYxY.jpg","original_title":"El campeón","original_language":"es"},{"id":276218,"adult":false,"title":"Arsène Lupin, Detective","video":false,"overview":"Arsène Lupin decides to run a detective agency in addition to being a gentleman thief. As a detective he happens to cooperate with police in order to unveil the criminal activities of a villain. When he succeeds the villain returns the favour. The unmasked Arsène Lupin manages to escape with the villain's gangster moll as his new companion.","genre_ids":[35,80,18],"popularity":0.1791,"vote_count":2,"poster_path":"/l5AzhZsTJzxWYekUTxApnF74pa5.jpg","release_date":"1937-04-30","vote_average":5.5,"backdrop_path":"/pgMdbvl6Gi0l9Sy4Pk2mYnkHr8m.jpg","original_title":"Arsène Lupin détective","original_language":"fr"},{"id":858871,"adult":false,"title":"Pochodně","video":false,"overview":"Prague in the 1870s. Work in Smolík's sulphur factory is hard and dangerous to health. The poorly paid workers resemble torches because their clothes are soaked with poisonous phosphorus. Young Josef Rezler also works in the sulphur factory and uses his earnings to feed his mother and little sisters. He throws his perpetually drunken father out of the house. The older worker Brož forces Josef to learn to read and write. A cholera epidemic breaks out in Prague and Josef is the only one of his family to survive the disease...","genre_ids":[18,36],"popularity":0.1634,"vote_count":1,"poster_path":"/3Fnyh3quR0M0Ep1bI2hF5NXmHDR.jpg","release_date":"1961-03-10","vote_average":5,"backdrop_path":null,"original_title":"Pochodně","original_language":"cs"},{"id":467425,"adult":false,"title":"Ravens","video":false,"overview":"A hard-working farmer, despairing by the harsh reality of his daily struggle, is determined to have his son taking over the farm and continue his legacy. The mother tries her best to keep the family together. Yet, with increasing horror, the son witnesses his father's psychotic behavior escalate.","genre_ids":[18],"popularity":2.2574,"vote_count":15,"poster_path":"/fHJ6ZRjvhG0AsfAndWcXLC0k1Fg.jpg","release_date":"2017-10-13","vote_average":6,"backdrop_path":"/cYkofKDoIjtUK3mBhjOo7J56Wvh.jpg","original_title":"Korparna","original_language":"sv"},{"id":5744,"adult":false,"title":"Fanny Hill","video":false,"overview":"Young, pretty and innocent, Fanny Hill has lost her parents and must find her way in life amidst the perils of turbulent 18th-century London. She's fortunate enough to rapidly find a place as chambermaid of the effusive Mrs. Brown, who lives in a large house teeming with female 'relatives' in negligée and with very relaxed manners. She also insists that Fanny alone meets various gentlemen who show an ardent interest in her.","genre_ids":[35,36],"popularity":0.6328,"vote_count":20,"poster_path":"/c8gcQ0MSymcqnvR4OQSngI6SgRP.jpg","release_date":"1964-09-25","vote_average":3.9,"backdrop_path":"/p77xULQxlVos1YnvtFbzOUebq4F.jpg","original_title":"Fanny Hill","original_language":"en"},{"id":5625,"adult":false,"title":"Madame and Her Niece","video":false,"overview":"Michelle De Winter lives the good life, wining and dining with only the richest men who are fortunate to cross her path. Her daughter Yvette, whom Michelle insists on introducing as her 'niece', is a fashion model. She is saving herself for the right man, despite the fact that she is part of the free love generation and lives with a group of promiscuous creative types. While Michelle is searching for a new millionaire playboy, Yvette falls for the handsome Peter Von Hallstein. She asks the fatherly Dr. Fink to help her come up with a scheme to get Peter to propose to he","genre_ids":[18],"popularity":0.3351,"vote_count":14,"poster_path":"/h4hyhY7qJG58mP9bokJUc9ItIBY.jpg","release_date":"1969-05-09","vote_average":4.571,"backdrop_path":"/wOESnxVhbZbnErSRcmKVgDRyexY.jpg","original_title":"Madame und ihre Nichte","original_language":"de"},{"id":9104,"adult":false,"title":"Buffalo Soldiers","video":false,"overview":"A criminal subculture operates among U.S. soldiers stationed in West Germany just before the fall of the Berlin wall.","genre_ids":[18,35,10752,80,53],"popularity":4.6762,"vote_count":344,"poster_path":"/qNl4T8xxC0xDeX8JFJVCBzH4Kg8.jpg","release_date":"2002-10-31","vote_average":6.281,"backdrop_path":"/7Pw5NOv7aUtmHyh1yASEldOlAz0.jpg","original_title":"Buffalo Soldiers","original_language":"en"},{"id":1258506,"adult":false,"title":"Fundvogel","video":false,"overview":"Young Jan Bergwall visits his grandmother, the so-called centenary, at Woyland Castle. There he meets his cousin Andrea, who everyone calls \"Fundvogel\". Jan is fascinated by the young girl's beauty, and soon there is an erotic tension in the air between the two. Although they both have strong feelings for each other, they are afraid to make a commitment, even though their domineering grandmother is determined that they marry. Panicked that he might feel obliged to marry Andrea, Jan escapes from this place. Andrea is deeply disappointed and seeks revenge. Out of spite, she becomes involved with the falconer Bartel and is later raped in a wooden hut. The centigress, concerned about morals and customs, then sends Fundvogel to a convent. She escapes from there and flees into the arms of Jan. When he learns from a letter from the countess what has happened to Andrea, he leaves her a second time. In her despair, Fundvogel then throws herself off a bridge into the floods with suicidal intent.","genre_ids":[18],"popularity":0.3905,"vote_count":0,"poster_path":"/t5JpoLpFsg1dAsMYedcZysyMF3d.jpg","release_date":"1930-05-19","vote_average":0,"backdrop_path":null,"original_title":"Fundvogel","original_language":"de"}],"external_ids":{"imdb_id":"tt28131433","twitter_id":null,"facebook_id":null,"wikidata_id":"Q130494024","instagram_id":null},"social_ids":{"twitter":null,"facebook":null,"instagram":null},"gdvg_id":110447,"wiki_plot":null,"wiki_synopsis":null,"wiki_episode_guide":null,"wiki_pr